                     <origDate when="1987">S. the colophon.</origDate>
                     <note>Ḫāyla Śǝllāse (ʾato Ṗarāqliṭos) is mentioned
                        as the donor of the Ms. in the colophon. His name is written in the
                        supplication formulas throughout the Ms., together with other individuals
                        (members of the community?), e.g. Gabra Madḫǝn (<locus target="#15vb">15vb</locus>), 
                        Gabra ʾAragāwi (<locus target="#16vb">16vb</locus>), Gabra
                        Māryām (<locus target="#4ra">4ra</locus>, 10vb), Walatta Ḥawāryāt (fol.
                        3vb).</note>
                  </origin>
                  
